        <abstract> 
<p>Questions CD’s view in <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi> that domestic dogs are not descended from a single stock. Occasional crossings of domestic stock with wild species could explain cases of reversion towards wild specific forms. CD’s views on hybridity do not then have to be contradicted in constructing an ancestral stock.</p> 
        </abstract>
